1. Service Account is used to authenticate a application which wants to communicate with the kube-api.
2. a. Creata a SA
   b. When a SA is created it creates the token also, which can be used as a bearer token by the application to get authenticated when tried to communicate with the kube-api.
   c. Token is stored as a secret object.

3. How to see the token.
   a. kubectl describe secret myapp-sa-token
